.
When a lot of people are writing their /hmofa/ story and they want to world build a little, they usually make it so humans and anthro are separated from one another and I have a problem with that
Now in some stories, there's nothing wrong with that, if the anthros came to existence after humans, maybe they were biologically engineered or maybe some event happened that led to them becoming a thing, or even maybe they are aliens from another planet, whatever
What's important is that there's an established and good reason for why humans and anthros of all types despite specie, are separated
But this to me, becomes problem when we aren't giving this reason at all in most normal stories, where human and anthros seem to have existed from the beginning it seems, with my head Saying "the separation wouldn't be like this".
I just don't see one single sub specie of apes (us) being separated into our own group, while every single other specie (including the rest of the apes) are in their own separate group that's somehow not split into different groups
I think a more realistic way to do it would be separation into multiple groups, based on specie, so all canines like wolfs and wild dogs and foxes would be together, all felines like tigers and lions and cats would fall together, and we (humans) would probably be in the group of primates with monkeys and lemurs and other apes.
I think beastars did something sorta like this in the background, while it had the "predators vs prey" thing in the center, for example, the main character was a wolf but his dorm room wasn't made up of only wolves, it had like two dogs, a fox and even a hyena.


So yeah uhhh Tl:dr your story not good because world building not realistic and I'm too autistic to suspend belief.
